        "timestamp": "2018-11-17 01:24:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Ok I have to be annoying and ask, did you make sure the other repos\n > compile? Notably drools-applications? :)\n\nHello Pam, Your question is justified because of multiple breaks yesterday. Until my last commit, i was never worried about other repos dependency while modifying a perticular repo. Because the code in one repo was not used in other repo. But in the last commit, EventProtocolCoder.enCoder method was used in the test files of the drools-application. \nHence i am more careful this time, while modifying the signature of the deCoder method, i went inside drools-application and looked for usage. Found no usage, Hence I was sure, this time, drools-application wont break :)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
